<paragraph id="2D02FD0E763E4203B9962D72FC8190E3" blockId="8.[166,1225,1226,1413]" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">
Remarks. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D763E4203B8A22D72FA7B9042" authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1960" box="[495,628,1290,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sinarachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C763E4203B8A22D72FA7B9042" box="[495,628,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">Sinarachna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="55AABD9E763E4203BA182D72FBBA9043" box="[853,949,1290,1317]" name="Ukraine" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
for the FIrst time. The two Ukrainian species can be distinguished as follows by the difference in pubescence of metasoma (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B763E4203B81C2D32F9999003" box="[337,406,1354,1381]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,205,1238,1260]" captionTargetBox="[265,1142,174,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-303@7.[265,1142,174,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Schizopyga and Sinarachna, ♀. 1–5 — Schizopyga: 1 — S. coxator, habitus (lateral view); 2 — S. circulator, face (frontal view);3 — S.coxator, face (frontal view);4 — S.coxator, pronotum (lateral view); 5 — S.circulator, pronotum (lateral view); 6–7 — Sinarachna, tergites III–IV of metasoma (dorsal view):6 — S. pallipes; 7 — S. nigricornis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449483/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">FIgs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C763E4203B8E92D32F9BD9002" box="[420,434,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">6</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C763E4203B88E2D32F9DE9002" box="[451,465,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">7</emphasis>
): densely pubescent in 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D763E4203BBA22D32FB869002" baseAuthorityName="Holmgren" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[751,905,1354,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sinarachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C763E4203BBA22D32FB869002" box="[751,905,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">S. nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and sparsely pubescent in 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D763E4203B9EB2D12F91690E2" baseAuthorityName="Holmgren" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[166,281,1386,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sinarachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipes">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C763E4203B9EB2D12F91690E2" box="[166,281,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">S. pallipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D763E4203B8852D12FA3590E2" baseAuthorityName="Holmgren" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[456,570,1386,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sinarachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipes">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C763E4203B8852D12FA3590E2" box="[456,570,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="375">S. pallipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has paler hind coxae and basal antennal segments.
</paragraph>
